snippet.textDisplay:
As an anime figure collector and anime fan, the only thing I can think of why they couldn't ship it to certain countries is licensing. THIS IS ONLY SPECULATION, NOT CONFIRMED BY COLOURPOP!!!!

Sailor Moon isn't licenced in certain countries, and sometimes the distributor is not allowed to sell a product based on characters owned by a brand that is owned by someone else. So ColourPop could have had an agreement with the licence holders in those certain countries, those brands got a portion of the cut, but the others didn't want a part of it or didn't want to be apart of it for whatever reason. They have the rights in certain countries, but not others. It happened to a figure of mine that I ordered and was cancelled. The North American licence holders didn't like the model for it and cancelled it throughout their licencing holder countries, so it became impossible to buy other than from Japan, where the licence was fine. That is kind of the only thing I can think of???? The Anime distribution world is a weird place, and it all comes down to who owns the rights.

snippet.textDisplay: My eyes swell from my autoimmune disease and they get so dry it’s revolting I use coconut 🥥 oil and straight aloe from my aloe plant. Works wonders. Sometimes I mix them putting the aloe on first but letting it dry it makes them feel very tight whereas the coconut oil does not. But I press it into my skin, two days of doing that and a magic trick of steaming them with hot water and sitting with oil on them or what I usually do sleeping with it on, really works!
